&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 21.74%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 1pt solid; BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=21%&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;12
990&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.88%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Purchase agreements&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;In order to mitigate the risks of volatility in commodity markets to which we are exposed
 we have entered into forward purchase agreements with certain suppliers based on market prices
 forward price projections and expected usage levels.&amp;#160; Our purchase commitments for certain ingredients
 packaging materials and energy are generally less than 12 months.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Licensing&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We produce T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s&amp;#174; brand snacks
 Tato Skins&amp;#174; brand potato crisps and Boulder Canyon&amp;#174; Natural Foods Rice and Bean snacks utilizing a sheeting and frying process that includes technology that we license from a third party.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement between us and the third party
 we have a royalty-bearing
 exclusive right license to use the technology in the United States
 Canada
 and Mexico until such time the parties mutually agree to terminate the agreement.&amp;#160; Even though the patents for this technology expired in December&amp;#160;2006
 in consideration for the use of this technology
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of products manufactured utilizing the technology until such termination date.&amp;#160; However
 should products substantially similar to Tato Skins&amp;#174;
 O&amp;#8217;Boisies&amp;#174; and Pizzarias&amp;#174; become available for any reason in the marketplace by any manufacturer other than us which results in a sales decline of 10% or more
 any royalty obligation for the respective products&amp;#160;shall cease.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We license the T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s&amp;#174; brand snacks trademark from T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s Inc. under a license agreement with a term expiring in May&amp;#160;2014.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s&amp;#174; brand snack products and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We license the Jamba&amp;#174; brand trademark from Jamba Juice Company under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2035.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Jamba&amp;#174; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We license the Nathan&amp;#8217;s Famous&amp;#174; brand trademark from Nathan&amp;#8217;s Famous Corporation under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2031.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Nathan&amp;#8217;s Famous&amp;#174; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We license the Vidalia&amp;#174; brand trademark from Vidalia Brands
&amp;#160;Inc. under a license agreement with a term expiring January&amp;#160;2019.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Vidalia&amp;#174; brand products during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We license the Seattle&amp;#8217;s Best Coffee&amp;#174; brand trademark from Seattle&amp;#8217;s Best Coffee LLC under a license agreement with a term expiring November&amp;#160;2017
 which automatically extends for a five-year period upon meeting certain minimum sales targets.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Seattle&amp;#8217;s Best Coffee&amp;#174; brand products during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Legal Proceedings&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We are periodically a party to various lawsuits arising in the ordinary course of business.&amp;#160; Management believes
 based on discussions with legal counsel
 that the resolution of any such lawsuits
 individually and in the aggregate
&amp;#160;will not have a material adverse effect on our financial position or results of operations.&amp;#160; See Note 12
 &amp;#8220;Litigation.&amp;#8221;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;9.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Stockholders&amp;#8217; Equity&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Restricted Stock Awards&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We have issued shares of restricted Common Stock as incentives to certain officers and members of our board of directors (the &amp;#8220;Board&amp;#8221;).&amp;#160; Restricted stock awards granted to officers contain performance restrictions that are required to be achieved over a three year measurement period in order for the shares to be awarded.&amp;#160; The number of performance-based restricted stock awards ultimately awarded varies based on whether we achieve certain financial results.&amp;#160; Restricted stock awards granted to members of the Board are granted with a one-year service period.&amp;#160; We record compensation expense each period based on the market price of our Common Stock at the time of grant and our estimate of the most probable number of awards issued under grants of performance-based restricted stock awards.&amp;#160; The related stock-based compensation expense is included in selling
 general and administrative expenses.&amp;#160; Additionally
 the compensation expense is adjusted for our estimate of forfeitures.&amp;#160; Recipients of restricted Common Stock are entitled to receive any dividends declared on our Common Stock and have voting rights
 regardless of whether such shares have vested.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The following table summarizes our restricted stock award activity during the year ended December&amp;#160;28
 2013:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

 2013
 December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 the total stock-based compensation expense from restricted stock recognized in the financial statements was $0.3 million
 $0.5 million and $0.6 million
 respectively.&amp;#160; There were no stock-based compensation costs which were capitalized.&amp;#160; As of December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 total unrecognized costs related to non-vested restricted stock awards granted is $0.4 million
 which is expected to be recognized over the next 0.85 years on a weighted-average basis.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Preferred Stock&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We have authorized 50
000 shares preferred stock
 $100 par value (&amp;#8220;Preferred Stock&amp;#8221;)
 none of which are outstanding.&amp;#160; We may issue such shares of Preferred Stock in the future without stockholder approval.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Stock Options&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The Company&amp;#8217;s Amended and Restated 2005 Equity Incentive Plan (the &amp;#8220;2005 Plan&amp;#8221;) was approved at our 2005 Annual Meeting of Stockholders
 and we initially reserved for issuance&amp;#160;410
518 shares of Common Stock.&amp;#160;&amp;#160; The number of shares of Common Stock reserved for issuance has been increased since 2005 to a total of 2
710
518 as of the date of this filing
 pursuant to a series of amendments to the 2005 Plan approved by our stockholders.&amp;#160; If any shares of Common Stock subject to awards granted under the 2005 Plan are canceled
 those shares will be available for future awards under the 2005 Plan.&amp;#160; The 2005 Plan expires in May&amp;#160;2015
 and awards granted under the 2005 Plan may include nonqualified stock options
 incentive stock options
 restricted stock
 restricted stock units
 stock appreciation rights
 performance units and stock-reference awards.&amp;#160; Prior to May&amp;#160;2008
 all stock option grants had a five-year term.&amp;#160; The fair value of these stock option grants is amortized to expense over the service period
 generally five years for employees and one year for members of the Board.&amp;#160; In May&amp;#160;2008
 our Board approved a 10-year term for all future stock option grants
 with service periods of five years for employees and one year for members of the Board.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 39pt; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;As of December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 there were 357
586 shares of Common Stock available for Awards under the 2005 Plan
 plus 743
316 shares of Common Stock available for any Awards under the 2005 Plan other than Incentive Stock Options.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The expected dividend yield was based on the fact that we have never issued a dividend and have no near term intent to do so.&amp;#160; The volatility assumption was based on historical volatility during the time period that corresponds to the expected life of the option.&amp;#160; The expected life (estimated period of time outstanding) of stock options granted was estimated based on historical exercise activity.&amp;#160; The risk-free interest rate assumption was based on the interest rate of U.S. Treasuries on the date the option was granted.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The total stock-based compensation expense from stock options recognized in the financial statements was $0.6 million
 $0.7 million and $0.4 million for the years ended December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively
 which reduced income from operations accordingly.&amp;#160; There were no stock-based compensation costs that were capitalized.&amp;#160; As of December&amp;#160;28
 2013 the total unrecognized costs related to non-vested stock options granted were $1.3 million.&amp;#160; We expect to recognize such costs in the financial statements over a weighted average period of 2.9 years.&amp;#160; This expected compensation expense does not reflect any new awards
 or modifications to existing awards
 that could occur in the future.&amp;#160; We issue new shares upon the exercise of stock options
 as opposed to reissuing treasury shares.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 0.78%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The weighted average grant-date fair value of options granted during the years ended December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011 were $3.90
 $3.57 and $2.44
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The intrinsic value related to total stock options outstanding was $8.3 million as of December&amp;#160;28
 2013 and $3.8 million as of December&amp;#160;29
 2012.&amp;#160; The intrinsic value related to vested stock options outstanding was $4.2 million as of December&amp;#160;28
 2013 and $2.6 million as of December&amp;#160;29
 2012.&amp;#160; The aggregate intrinsic value is based on the exercise price and our closing stock price of $13.47 as of December&amp;#160;28
 2013 and $6.31 as of December&amp;#160;29
 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Treasury Stock&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Our Board of Directors approved a stock repurchase program that was publicly announced on Form&amp;#160;8-K filed with the SEC on June&amp;#160;21
 2011 whereby up to $3.0 million of common stock could be purchased from time to time at the discretion of management (the &amp;#8220;2011 program&amp;#8221;).&amp;#160; The 2011 program expired on June&amp;#160;20
 2012.&amp;#160; No shares were repurchased under the 2011 program.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;10&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; Income Taxes&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The provision for income taxes consisted of the following for the years ended December&amp;#160;28

&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 2.78%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=2%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;%&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 13.34%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=13% colspan=2&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;34.9&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.08%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;%&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;11.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Business Segments and Significant Customers&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;For the years ended December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 Costco was the only customer accounting for more than 10% of our total net revenue.&amp;#160; Costco accounted for $74.5 million
 or 35% of our total net revenue; $64.6 million
 or 35% of our total net revenue; and $49.3 million
 or 30% or our total net revenue; for fiscal years 2013
 2012 and 2011
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Our operations consist of two reportable segments: frozen products and snack products.&amp;#160; The frozen products segment produces frozen fruits
 vegetables and beverages for sale primarily to groceries
 club stores and mass merchandisers.&amp;#160; The snack products segment produces potato chips
 kettle chips
 potato crisps
 potato skins
 pellet snacks
 sheeted dough products and extruded products for sale primarily to snack food distributors and retailers.&amp;#160; Our reportable segments offer different products and services.&amp;#160; The majority of our revenues are attributable to external customers in the United States.&amp;#160; We also sell to external customers internationally; however
 the revenues attributable to such customers are immaterial.&amp;#160; All of our assets are located in the United States.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The accounting policies of our reportable segments are the same as those described in &amp;#8220;Note 1.&amp;#160; Summary of Significant Accounting Policies.&amp;#8221;&amp;#160; We do not allocate assets
 selling
 general and administrative expenses
 income taxes or other income and expense to our reportable segments. The following tables present information about our reportable segments for the quarters and year ended December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011 (in thousands):&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;12.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Litigation&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We are periodically a party to various lawsuits arising in the ordinary course of business.&amp;#160; Management believes
 based on discussions with legal counsel
 that the resolution of any such lawsuits
 individually and in the aggregate
&amp;#160;will not have a material adverse effect on our financial position or results of operations.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Under our license agreement with the Jamba Juice Company (&amp;#8220;Jamba Juice&amp;#8221;)
 we are obligated and have agreed to indemnify and defend Jamba Juice in the two matters identified herein
 and Jamba Juice has tendered defense of these matters to us.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;In March&amp;#160;2012
 we learned that Jamba Juice was named as a defendant in a putative class action filed in the Federal Court for the North District of California and captioned &lt;i&gt;Anderson v. Jamba Juice Company&lt;/i&gt; (the &amp;#8220;Anderson Matter&amp;#8221;).&amp;#160; The plaintiff purports to represent a class of individuals who purchased make-at-home smoothie kits from Jamba Juice
 and alleges that such smoothie kits contain unnaturally processed
 synthetic and/or non-natural ingredients and that use of the words &amp;#8220;All Natural&amp;#8221; on the labels of these smoothie kits is unfair and fraudulent and violates various false advertising and unfair competition laws.&amp;#160; The Anderson Matter is one of several &amp;#8220;all natural&amp;#8221; lawsuits recently brought against various food manufacturers and distributors in California.&amp;#160; In an amended complaint
 the plaintiff also alleged violations of the federal Magnuson-Moss Warranty Act
 but the court dismissed those claims in August&amp;#160;2012.&amp;#160; In a second amended complaint filed in September&amp;#160;2012
 we were added as a defendant.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the parties&amp;#8217; stipulation
 on September&amp;#160;3
 2013 the court dismissed the Anderson Matter.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;On June&amp;#160;28
 2013 a class action complaint against Jamba Juice and the Company
 captioned &lt;i&gt;Lilly v. Jamba Juice Company et al&lt;/i&gt; (the &amp;#8220;Lilly Matter&amp;#8221;)
 was filed in the Federal Court for the Northern District of California and makes nearly identical allegations as those made in the Anderson Matter
 except that the complaint also alleges that the smoothie kits contain two additional allegedly non-natural ingredients.&amp;#160; The plaintiffs in this new action are represented by the same counsel that represented the plaintiff in the Anderson Matter. While we currently believe the &amp;#8220;all natural&amp;#8221; statement on the smoothie kits are not misleading and in full compliance with FDA guidelines
 we are investigating the claims asserted in the Lilly Matter
 and intend to vigorously defend against them.&amp;#160; On September&amp;#160;17
 2013
 we filed a motion to dismiss
 seeking to dismiss plaintiffs&amp;#8217; claims as to gelatin and the Orange Dream Machine smoothie kit.&amp;#160; Our motion was denied in November&amp;#160;2013.&amp;#160; On February&amp;#160;4
 2014
 the plaintiffs filed a motion to certify a class of all persons in California who bought certain smoothie kits from Jamba Juice.&amp;#160; The parties have agreed to attempt to resolve this action
 and have set a March&amp;#160;31
 2014 mediation date.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;On February&amp;#160;13
 2014
 plaintiff Vanessa Montantes filed two putative class lawsuits against the Company in federal and state court located in the Los Angeles
 California.&amp;#160; In the lawsuits
 plaintiff alleges that the Company violated California law by recording certain telephone calls made to its consumer affairs telephone number without providing sufficient notice.&amp;#160;&amp;#160; The Company has not been served with process in either lawsuit and is investigating the allegations.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;13.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Related Party Transactions&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We lease 840 acres of farming land in Whatcom County
 Washington
 of which 696 acres are leased from the Uptrails Group LLC
 which is owned by three members of the Rader family.&amp;#160; Our processing and storage facilities are located on the land leased from the Uptrails Group LLC.&amp;#160; One of the three members
 Brad Rader
 is a current employee of ours and one of the other members
 Sue Rader
 was a former owner of Rader Farms.&amp;#160; This operating lease commenced on the acquisition date and was extended in October&amp;#160;2012 through May&amp;#160;17
 2027.&amp;#160; Lease payments to us are $43
500 per month through May&amp;#160;17
 2017 at which time they increase to $52
200 for the duration of the term of the lease.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Effective January&amp;#160;13
 2013
 a member of our Board was named Chief Executive Officer of Bland Farms
&amp;#160;Inc.
 the parent company of Vidalia Brands
&amp;#160;Inc.
 with whom we have a broker agreement and a license to sell our Vidalia&amp;#174; brand snack products.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;14.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Accounts Receivable Allowance&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;132&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 3%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=3%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 14.42%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=14%&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;(21&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 3%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=3%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.3%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 13.12%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=13%&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;220&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.1%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;15.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Concentrations of Credit Risk&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We maintain most of our cash with one financial institution.&amp;#160; As of November&amp;#160;1
 2008
 the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (&amp;#8220;FDIC&amp;#8221;) introduced the transaction guarantee program which guaranteed non-interest bearing accounts without limit.&amp;#160; The FDIC program is temporary and only offered through participating financial institutions.&amp;#160; Our primary financial institution participated in this program and
 therefore
 all cash balances held with this institution as of December&amp;#160;28
 2013 are insured.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Our primary concentration of credit risk is related to certain trade accounts receivable.&amp;#160; In the normal course of business
 we extend unsecured credit to our customers.&amp;#160; We investigate a customer&amp;#8217;s credit worthiness before extending credit.&amp;#160; At December&amp;#160;28
 2013 and December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 three customers accounted for 35% and 48% of accounts receivable
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;16.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Deferred Compensation Plans&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We have contributory 401(k)&amp;#160;plans covering substantially all of our employees.&amp;#160; We may contribute amounts not in excess of the lesser of the maximum deductions allowable for income tax purposes or a specific percentage of our operating profits
 as defined in the plan.&amp;#160; We made contributions totaling $0.5 million
 $0.4 million and $0.4 million during the years ending December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;We also sponsor a trusteed
 nonqualified savings plan for employees whose contributions to a tax qualified 401(k)&amp;#160;plan would be limited by provisions of the Internal Revenue Code.&amp;#160; The plan allows participants to defer receipt of a portion of their salary and incentive compensation.&amp;#160; The plan was amended in 2009
 and we no longer match any employee contributions to this plan.&amp;#160; Participants earn a return on their deferred compensation based on investment earnings of participant-selected mutual funds.&amp;#160; Deferred compensation
 including accumulated earnings on the participant-directed investment selections
 is distributable in cash at participant-specified dates or upon retirement
 death
 disability or termination of employment.&amp;#160; At December&amp;#160;28
 2013 and December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 the plan&amp;#8217;s assets and our liability to participants of the deferred compensation plans was $0.6 million and $0.4 million
 respectively
 and is recorded in other assets and other liabilities in the Consolidated Balance Sheets.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Principles of Consolidation&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of Inventure Foods
&amp;#160;Inc. and all of its wholly owned subsidiaries.&amp;#160; All significant intercompany amounts and transactions have been eliminated.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Our fiscal year ends on the last Saturday occurring in the month of December&amp;#160;of each calendar year.&amp;#160; Accordingly
 the fiscal year end dates result in an additional week of results every five or six years.&amp;#160; Fiscal year 2013 commenced December&amp;#160;30
 2012 and ended December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&amp;#160; Fiscal year 2012 commenced January&amp;#160;1
 2012 ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&amp;#160; Fiscal year 2011 commenced December&amp;#160;26
 2010 ended December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 resulting in a 53-week fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Use of Estimates&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The preparation of financial statements in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States (&amp;#8220;GAAP&amp;#8221;) requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities
 disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements
 and the reported amounts of revenue and expenses during the reporting period.&amp;#160; We routinely evaluate our estimates
 including those related to accruals for customer programs and incentives
 product returns
 bad debts
 income taxes
 long-lived assets
 inventories
 stock-based compensation
 interest rate swap valuations
 accrued broker commissions and contingencies.&amp;#160; We base our estimates on historical experience and on various other assumptions that are believed to be reasonable under the circumstances.&amp;#160; Actual results could differ from those estimates.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Fair Value of Financial Instruments&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.4in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Fair value is defined as the price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability (i.e.
 the &amp;#8220;exit price&amp;#8221;) in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date.&amp;#160; W&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;e classify our investments based upon an established fair value hierarchy that prioritizes the inputs to valuation techniques used to measure fair value.&amp;#160; The hierarchy gives the highest priority to unadjusted quoted prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities (Level 1 measurement) and the lowest priority to unobservable inputs (Level 3 measurement).&amp;#160; The three levels of the fair value hierarchy are described as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.4in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table style=text-align:left;WIDTH: 94.66%; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; MARGIN-LEFT: 0.4in; border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=94%&gt;
&lt;tr style=padding:0;&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 9.06%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=9%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Level 1&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.34%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 89.62%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=89%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Unadjusted quoted prices in active markets that are accessible at the measurement date for identical
 unrestricted assets or liabilities.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr style=padding:0;&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 9.06%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=9%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.34%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 89.62%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=89%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr style=padding:0;&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 9.06%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=9%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Level 2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.34%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 89.62%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=89%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Quoted prices in markets that are not considered to be active or financial instruments without quoted market prices
 but for which all significant inputs are observable
 either directly or indirectly.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr style=padding:0;&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 9.06%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=9%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.34%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 89.62%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=89%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr style=padding:0;&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 9.06%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=9%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; size=2&gt;Level 3&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.34%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 89.62%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=top width=89%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Prices or valuations that require inputs that are both significant to the fair value measurement and unobservable.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: -1in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 1.4in;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.4in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;A financial instrument&amp;#8217;s level within the fair value hierarchy is based on the lowest level of any input that is significant to the fair value measurement.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;At December&amp;#160;28
 2013 and December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 the carrying value of cash
 accounts receivable
 accounts payable and accrued liabilities approximate fair values since they are short term in nature.&amp;#160; The carrying value of the long-term debt approximates fair value based on the borrowing rates currently available to us for long-term borrowings with similar terms. The following table summarized the valuation of our assets and liabilities measured at fair value on a recurring basis (in thousands):&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: -10pt; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 10pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Other assets&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 2%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=2%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 10%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=10%&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Level 1&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 2%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=2%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 8.7%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 1pt solid; BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=8%&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;&amp;#8212;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 2%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=2%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1.3%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; BORDER-TOP: medium none; BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=1%&gt;

&lt;p style=TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;&amp;#8212;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 1%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-TOP: 0in; bgcolor=#CCEEFF valign=bottom width=1%&gt;

&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Considerable judgment is required in interpreting market data to develop the estimate of fair value of our derivative instruments.&amp;#160; Accordingly
 the estimate may not be indicative of the amounts that we could realize in a current market exchange.&amp;#160; The use of different market assumptions or valuation methodologies could have a material effect on the estimated fair value amounts.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;Our non-qualified deferred compensation plan assets consist of money market and mutual funds invested in domestic and international marketable securities that are directly observable in active markets.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;The fair value measurement of the earn-out contingent consideration obligation relates to the acquisition of Willamette Valley Fruit Company in May&amp;#160;2013 and Fresh Frozen Foods in November&amp;#160;2013
 and is included in accrued liabilities and other long-term liabilities in the consolidated balance sheets.&amp;#160; The fair value measurement is based upon significant inputs not observable in the market.&amp;#160; Changes in the value of the obligation are recorded as income or expense in our consolidated statements of income.&amp;#160; We estimated the original fair value of the contingent consideration as the present value of the expected contingent payments
 determined using the weighted probabilities of the possible payments.&amp;#160; We are required to reassess the fair value of the contingent payments on a contingent basis.&amp;#160; Significant increases (decreases) in any of those probabilities in isolation may result in a higher (lower) fair value measurement.&amp;#160; The significant inputs used in these estimates include numerous possible scenarios for the payments based on the contractual terms of the contingent consideration
 for which probabilities are assigned to each scenario
 which are then discounted based on an individual risk analysis of the respective liabilities (weighted average discount rate of 5.4% for the outstanding liabilities as of December&amp;#160;28
 2013).&amp;#160; Although we believe our assumptions are reasonable
 different assumptions or changes in the future may result in different estimated amounts.&amp;#160; A one percentage point change in the discount rates used would not have significantly impacted the recorded liability as of December&amp;#160;28
 2013.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; size=2&gt;A summary of the activity of the fair value of the measurements using unobservable inputs (Level 3 Liabilities) for the year ended December&amp;#160;28
 2013
 is as follows (in thousands):&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; WIDTH: 3.4%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; valign=bottom width=3%&gt;
